						<summary>

						<p>Stone set up near the house of Hiregauḍa.</p>						

						<p>16th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is a damaged inscription. It states that a gift [of land] was made by Timmapa-nāyaka for having dug a well at Suḷa.</p>						

						<p>The record belongs to about 16th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
